						               													<description>Astroid: &amp;#208;&amp;#147;&amp;#208;&amp;#187;&amp;#208;&amp;#176;&amp;#208;&amp;#180;&amp;#208;&amp;#184;&amp;#208;&amp;#176;&amp;#209;&amp;#130;&amp;#208;&amp;#190;&amp;#209;&amp;#128;&amp;#209;&amp;#139; &amp;#208;&amp;#177;&amp;#209;&amp;#131;&amp;#208;&amp;#180;&amp;#209;&amp;#131;&amp;#209;&amp;#137;&amp;#208;&amp;#181;&amp;#208;&amp;#179;&amp;#208;&amp;#190;, Astroids: Gladiators of the Future is a tactical board game with collectible miniatures of fighting robots: Astroids.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Astroids are easily assembled without glue and can be painted with any model paints. &amp;#10;The set of the game includes 12 collectible miniatures of astroid robots, 12 armlists, elements for assembling fortifications, three cubes, two cardboard rulers, 40 sliding arrows, a legend, assembly instructions and rules of the game in Russian.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Astroids are remotely controlled robots designed specifically for heavy work on asteroids. They are equipped with a control computer, a biosensor unit, which allows you to control the robot using a &amp;ldquo;biopotential&amp;rdquo; helmet and overalls. When there were a lot of Astroid robots, and the demand for them fell, gladiatorial battles of Asteroids with a sweepstakes began to be very popular. Choose a squad of Astroid robots and test your robot control skills and win the arena.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;To start playing, place various objects - books, boxes, building blocks and other elements. &amp;#10;When the field is ready, choose the edge of the field from which to start the game and place your robots no further than 10 cm from the edge. &amp;#10;Place your Robots' armlists next to it. &amp;#10;To determine who will go first, all players roll a dice, the one with the highest result will go first, then clockwise.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The player who is the first to destroy all enemies is declared the winner.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;ndash;user summary&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
